defaultBusesdefaultCurrently the parish is served by a half hour bus service seven days a week (no 10) operated by Go North East.  This is a good service but runs along the A695 and does not ser
defaultve the other parts of the parish.
default&#xa0;
defaultThe only other regular commercial service is the 
default613 between 
defaultWhittonstall
default and Hexham which travels around 
defaultStocksfield
default and some of its satellite communities.   Thi
defaults bus only operates on Tuesdays and is a much valued weekly
default service to an unsustainable community.
default&#xa0;
defaultIn the recent past the route from 
defaultWhittonstall
default to Branch End (
defaultStocksfield
default) was served by a service on a weekday basis (2 buses a day each way) to Newcastle.
default&#xa0;
defaultIn the distant past New Ridley was served by a regular se
defaultrvice to Newcastle which operated 7 days a week and 3-6 times a day from early morning to late at night.
default&#xa0;
defaultFor many of the residents in the parish of 
defaultBroomley
default &amp; 
defaultStocksfield
default the current bus route is up to 20 minutes walk from their homes.   In the satellite 
defaultsettlements this route is only accessible by car or bike.
default&#xa0;
defaultMany of the residents of New Ridley and New Ridley Road in particular form part of our aging population and once they are unable to drive will be isolated in their homes as the bus service does not
default meet their needs.  New Ridley is 1.5 miles from the A695 (a good 40 minute walk for a fit person
default)
default and the southern parts of New Ridley Road are also up to a 30 minute walk from the A695.
